    • visitLegacyFetchBuilders

      public void visitLegacyFetchBuilders(Consumer<LegacyFetchBuilder> resultBuilderConsumer)
      Description copied from interface: ResultSetMapping
      Visit the "legacy" fetch builders.

      Historically these mappings in Hibernate were defined such that results and fetches are unaware of each other. So while ResultBuilder encapsulates the fetches (see ResultBuilder.visitFetchBuilders(java.util.function.BiConsumer<org.hibernate.sql.results.graph.Fetchable, org.hibernate.query.results.FetchBuilder>)), fetches defined in the legacy way are unassociated to their "parent".

      Specified by:
      visitLegacyFetchBuilders in interface ResultSetMapping
